{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FHHus1zLP8QLWp9iokzAC7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error says: \"Reconfig attempted to install a config that would change the implicit default write concern. Use the setDefaultRWConcern command to set a cluster-wide write concern and try the reconfig again.\"\n\nThis happens when going from 2 data-bearing members (PSS config - all votes from data-bearing members) to a PSA (Primary-Secondary-Arbiter) config. When you have a PSA setup, MongoDB's default write concern behavior changes, and it raises this error to prevent accidentally breaking write concern guarantees.\n\nThe fix is to first set the cluster-wide write concern, then add the arbiter. \n\nFor a PSA setup, I need to set `{ w: 1 }` as the default write concern since with an arbiter present, majority acknowledgment would require at least one of the two data-bearing members to acknowledge, which is more restrictive than necessary.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":507,"cache_read_input_tokens":31578,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":507},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e78970c6-ff55-47ff-8868-93ea976cde49","uuid":"a9d2669e-fdce-4c0c-8cfc-798ff1c67fcd","request_id":"req_011CcMqkaVDBnqsppF2XwDnS"}
